ents":0,"created_at":"2025-12-12T10:29:19Z","updated_at":"2025-12-13T01:16:06Z","closed_at":"2025-12-13T01:16:06Z","assignee":{"login":"dahlia","id":12431,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNDMx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/12431?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dahlia","html_url":"https://github.com/dahlia","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dahlia/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dahlia/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dahlia/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dahlia/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dahlia/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dahlia/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dahlia/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dahlia/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dahlia/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Summary\n\nAdd a Koa adapter package (`@logtape/koa`) that provides HTTP request logging middleware for Koa applications using LogTape as the logging backend, as an alternative to the `koa-logger` middleware.\n\n## Background\n\n[Koa](https://koajs.com/) is a modern, lightweight web framework for Node.js created by the team behind Express. It leverages async functions to eliminate callback nesting and provides an elegant middleware composition model. Koa has over 35 million weekly downloads on npm and is used by approximately 33% of Node.js developers according to recent surveys.\n\nFor HTTP request logging, Koa applications typically use [koa-logger](https://github.com/koajs/logger), which provides development-style logging middleware. According to koa-logger's documentation:\n\n- It logs incoming requests and outgoing responses with timing information\n- Output format: `<-- GET /` and `--> GET / 200 835ms 746b`\n- Supports custom transporter functions for redirecting log output\n\n```javascript\napp.use(logger((str, args) => {\n  // redirect koa logger to other output pipe\n  // args: [format, method, url, status, time, length]\n}))\n```\n\nWhile koa-logger can redirect output via the transporter function, this requires manual integration and doesn't provide native LogTape features. A dedicated LogTape middleware would offer seamless structured logging.\n\n## Proposed API\n\n```typescript\nimport Koa from \"koa\";\nimport { configure } from \"@logtape/logtape\";\nimport { koaLogger } from \"@logtape/koa\";\n\nawait configure({\n  // ... LogTape configuration\n});\n\nconst app = new Koa();\n\n// Basic usage - should be used near the top to wrap all subsequent middleware\napp.use(koaLogger());\n\n// With options\napp.use(koaLogger({\n  category: [\"myapp\", \"http\"],\n  level: \"info\",\n}));\n\napp.use((ctx) => {\n  ctx.body = { hello: \"world\" };\n});\n```\n\n## Implementation details\n\n### Middleware functionality\n\nThe adapter needs to provide request logging similar to koa-logger but using LogTape:\n\n| Feature | koa-logger | LogTape adapter |\n|---------|-----------|-----------------|\n| Request logging | `<-- GET /` | Structured `request` log |\n| Response logging | `--> GET / 200 835ms 746b` | Structured `response` log |\n| HTTP method | `args[1]` | `method` property |\n| URL path | `args[2]` | `url` property |\n| Status code | `args[3]` | `status` property |\n| Response time | `args[4]` | `responseTime` property |\n| Content length | `args[5]` | `contentLength` property |\n\n### Koa middleware pattern\n\nKoa uses an \"onion\" middleware model where control flows downstream through `await next()` and then back upstream. This is ideal for request/response logging:\n\n```typescript\n// Internal implementation concept\nfunction koaLogger(options?: KoaLogTapeOptions) {\n  const logger = getLogger(options?.category ?? [\"koa\"]);\n\n  return async (ctx, next) => {\n    const startTime = Date.now();\n\n    // Log incoming request\n    logger.debug(\"Incoming request\", {\n      method: ctx.method,\n      url: ctx.url,\n    });\n\n    try {\n      await next();\n    } finally {\n      const responseTime = Date.now() - startTime;\n\n      // Log response\n      logger.info(\"Request completed\", {\n        method: ctx.method,\n        url: ctx.url,\n        status: ctx.status,\n        responseTime,\n        contentLength: ctx.response.length,\n      });\n    }\n  };\n}\n```\n\n### Key challenges\n\n1. **Upstream/downstream logging**: koa-logger logs both the incoming request (`<--`) and outgoing response (`-->`). The adapter should support this pattern while keeping structured logging as the default.\n\n2. **Error handling**: Koa's error handling flows through middleware, so the adapter should properly handle and log errors that occur downstream.\n\n3. **Context properties**: Koa's context (`ctx`) contains rich information. The adapter should expose relevant properties while avoiding sensitive data.\n\n4. **Middleware position**: The documentation should emphasize placing the logger near the top of the middleware stack to properly wrap all subsequent middleware.\n\n### Proposed options interface\n\n```typescript\ninterface KoaLogTapeOptions {\n  /**\n   * The LogTape category to use. Defaults to [\"koa\"].\n   */\n  category?: string | readonly string[];\n\n  /**\n   * The log level for successful requests. Defaults to \"info\".\n   */\n  level?: \"debug\" | \"info\" | \"warning\" | \"error\";\n\n  /**\n   * Whether to log incoming requests (upstream). Defaults to false.\n   * When true, logs at debug level when request arrives.\n   */\n  logRequest?: boolean;\n\n  /**\n   * Function to determine if logging should be skipped.\n   */\n  skip?: (ctx: Context) => boolean;\n\n  /**\n   * Custom function to extract additional properties from context.\n   */\n  getProperties?: (ctx: Context) => Record<string, unknown>;\n}\n```\n\n## Benefits\n\n- Koa users can leverage LogTape's features: zero dependencies, hierarchical categories, structured logging, context management\n- Libraries using LogTape will have their logs unified with Koa's request logging\n- Enables LogTape's \"fingers crossed\" sink pattern for Koa request debugging\n- Native structured logging without ANSI color code processing\n- Seamless integration with Koa's async middleware model\n\n## Related\n\n- Koa official website: https://koajs.com/\n- koa-logger GitHub repository: https://github.com/koajs/logger\n- koa-logger npm package: https://www.npmjs.com/package/koa-logger\n- Existing adapter: `@logtape/fastify`","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dahlia/logtape/issues/106/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dahlia/logtape/issues/106/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koajs/koa/issues/1600","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koajs/koa","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koajs/koa/issues/1600/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koajs/koa/issues/1600/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koajs/koa/issues/1600/events","html_url":"https://github.com/koajs/koa/issues/1600","id":1027069205,"node_id":"I_kwDOALBDMs49N9UV","number":1600,"title":"The context can not work with _.cloneDeep","user":{"login":"xiedacon","id":14571125,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0NTcxMTI1","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/14571125?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/xiedacon","html_url":"https://github.com/xiedacon","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/xiedacon/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/xiedacon/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/xiedacon/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/xiedacon/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/xiedacon/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/xiedacon/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/xiedacon/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/xiedacon/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/xiedacon/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":7,"created_at":"2021-10-15T04:30:19Z","updated_at":"2026-02-02T03:18:56Z","closed_at":"2024-09-20T13:24:02Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Test codes:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst _ = require('lodash');\r\nconst Koa = require('koa');\r\n\r\nconst app = new Koa();\r\n\r\napp.use((ctx) => {\r\n    _.cloneDeep(ctx);\r\n\r\n    ctx.body = {\r\n        test: 'test',\r\n    };\r\n});\r\n\r\napp.listen(3000);\r\n```\r\n\r\n```sh\r\ncurl http://127.0.0.1:3000/\r\n```\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n  TypeError: Cannot read property 'length' of undefined\r\n      at Object.length (/Users/admin/Downloads/test/node_modules/delegates/index.js:72:24)\r\n      at isArrayLike (/Users/admin/Downloads/test/node_modules/lodash/lodash.js:11401:46)\r\n      at keys (/Users/admin/Downloads/test/node_modules/lodash/lodash.js:13375:14)\r\n      at baseGetAllKeys (/Users/admin/Downloads/test/node_modules/lodash/lodash.js:3094:20)\r\n      at getAllKeys (/Users/admin/Downloads/test/node_modules/lodash/lodash.js:5916:14)\r\n      at baseClone (/Users/admin/Downloads/test/node_modules/lodash/lodash.js:2726:39)\r\n      at /Users/admin/Downloads/test/node_modules/lodash/lodash.js:2733:34\r\n      at arrayEach (/Users/admin/Downloads/test/node_modules/lodash/lodash.js:530:11)\r\n      at baseClone (/Users/admin/Downloads/test/node_modules/lodash/lodash.js:2727:7)\r\n      at /Users/admin/Downloads/test/node_modules/lodash/lodash.js:2733:34\r\n```\r\n\r\nI found it was caused by the code here https://github.com/koajs/koa/blob/19f3353e5da6a0d52fb968a9429523585e42a288/lib/context.js\r\n\r\nThe simple code is like this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst _ = require('lodash');\r\n\r\nconst contextProto = {};\r\n// delegates\r\nObject.defineProperty(contextProto, 'length', {\r\n    get: function () {\r\n        return this.response.length;\r\n    },\r\n    set: function (val) {\r\n        this.response.length = val;\r\n    },\r\n});\r\n\r\n// new App()\r\nconst app = {\r\n    context: Object.create(contextProto),\r\n};\r\n\r\n// new ctx\r\nconst ctx = Object.create(app.context);\r\nctx.app = app;\r\nctx.response = { length: 1 };\r\n\r\nconsole.log(_.cloneDeep(ctx));\r\n// console.log(_.cloneDeep(app));\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen execute `_.cloneDeep(ctx)`, `app` will also be cloned. But `app.context` can not be clone, because `lodash` needs the `length` proproty to decide whether obj is array-like https://github.com/lodash/lodash/blob/2da024c3b4f9947a48517639de7560457cd4ec6c/isArrayLike.js\r\n\r\n> It also happens on [request](https://github.com/koajs/koa/blob/19f3353e5da6a0d52fb968a9429523585e42a288/lib/request.js) and [response](https://github.com/koajs/koa/blob/19f3353e5da6a0d52fb968a9429523585e42a288/lib/response.js).\r\n\r\nI think maybe we should do some special operations for `length` property, just like this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst _ = require('lodash');\r\n\r\nconst contextProto = {};\r\n// delegates\r\nObject.defineProperty(contextProto, 'length', {\r\n    get: function () {\r\n        return this.response?.length;\r\n    },\r\n    set: function (val) {\r\n        if (this.response) {\r\n            this.response.length = val;\r\n        }\r\n    },\r\n});\r\n\r\n// new App()\r\nconst app = {\r\n    context: Object.create(contextProto),\r\n};\r\n\r\n// new ctx\r\nconst ctx = Object.create(app.context);\r\nctx.app = app;\r\nctx.response = { length: 1 };\r\n\r\nconsole.log(_.cloneDeep(ctx));\r\n// console.log(_.cloneDeep(app));\r\n```\r\n\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koajs/koa/issues/1600/reactions","total_count":6,"+1":6,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koajs/koa/issues/1600/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Kadajett/prism-pipe/issues/1","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Kadajett/prism-pipe","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Kadajett/prism-pipe/issues/1/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Kadajett/prism-pipe/issues/1/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Kadajett/prism-pipe/issues/1/events","html_url":"https://github.com/Kadajett/prism-pipe/issues/1","id":4042505791,"node_id":"I_kwDORhg7Gc7w874_","number":1,"title":"Research: Pipeline & Composition Layer Architecture for Prism Pipe","user":{"login":"Kadajett","id":3784716,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM3ODQ3MTY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3784716?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Kadajett","html_url":"https://github.com/Kadajett","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Kadajett/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Kadajett/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Kadajett/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Kadajett/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Kadajett/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://ap